|   0.10  | 16.10.95 | First public release                                  |
+---------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|   0.15  | 07.12.95 | - Added input-mode:                                   |
|         |          |   each single address can be entered by hand, without |
|         |          |   any list needed                                     |
+---------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|   0.20  | 08.12.95 | - Added tearline                                      |
|         |          | - Added support for emails and gateways               |
|         |          | - Small cosmetical fixes to the guide                 |
+---------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|   0.25  | 02.01.96 | - Corrected tearline to fit FTN-specifications        |
|         |          | - Deletion of temporary-files when successful finished|
|         |          |   added                                               |
|         |          | - Alternate CC:-header-style when wildcard-search was |
|         |          |   used (pattern instead of names)                     |
|         |          | - Improved nodelist-support                           |
|         |          | - Now automatically deletes yourself as a receiver    |
|         |          | - Bugfix: last node in list can now be deleted        |
|         |          | - Bugfix: in wildcard-mode sending of the message now |
|         |          |   works when there is only one receiver who had more  |
|         |          |   than one nodelist-entry                             |
+---------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|   0.27  | 14.02.96 | - Removed nasty bug in the mailing-list function      |
|         |          |   (messages were always sent to "Unknown" when the    |
|         |          |   address was not listed in a nodelist, even if there |
|         |          |   was a name given in the mailing-list)               |
|         |          | - Added german main-program and documentation         |
|         |          | - Several small corrections in the docs               |
+---------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|   0.30  | 26.02.96 | - Bugfix: some netmails to FTN-addresses have not been|
|         |          |   sent                                                |
|         |          | - Bugfix: FTN-netmails did not have a receiver-name   |
|         |          | - Implemented posting in areatags                     |
|         |          | - New config-keyword: #ECHOREC for areatag-receiver-  |
|         |          |   name                                                |
|         |          | - Now there are return-receipts for netmails possible |
|         |          | - Included history-file in the guide                  |
|         |          | - Overall-optimization of the program                 |
+---------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+
|   0.35  | 02.05.96 | - Bugfix: sometimes you have not been asked if you    |
|         |          |   would like to save the list when changes have been  |
|         |          |   made                                                |
|         |          | - New keywords:  #ZONE and #NET for better support of |
|         |          |   network-files when using wildcard-mode              |
|         |          | - New keyword: #UNKNOWN for the default name of un-   |
|         |          |   listed sites                                        |
|         |          | - Now supports realnames for RFC-receivers in the CC:-|
|         |          |   header (see format of lists/inputs)                 |
|         |          | - Now there are unique echo-receivers for each area   |
|         |          |   possible (see format of lists/inputs)               |
|         |          | - Fixed two little "bugs" in the guide                |
|         |          | - Listview-handling changed to work with MM 1.2       |
+---------+----------+-------------------------------------------------------+
